$ Stellarium API: core.selectObjectByName

code {
core.selectObjectByName(
 'Venus'  , // The english name of the object to be selected
  true      // If the pointer needs to be enabled
);
code }

{ Pointer

  An enabled «pointer» (second argument) refers to the the four red somewhat glowing lines around the selected object:
  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/img/selectObjectByName.png||

}

sa:

  What (that is: how much) object related data is shown when an object is select can be configured in → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/GUI/popups/Configuration/Information[Configuration->Information].
  -
  The corresponding Script API function is → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setSelectedObjectInfo[`core.setSelectedObjectInfo`].

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/getObjectPosition[`core.getObjectPosition()`]

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/StelMovementMgr/setFlagTracking[`StelMovementMgr.setFlagTracking(true)`] goes to the selected object and tracks it.

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API
